England":"英國戴文迪維頓","Truro, Cornwall, England, United Kingdom":"英國英格蘭可瓦爾特魯羅","Hittsleigh, Devon, England":"英國英格蘭戴文希迪斯利","Hutenesleigh, Devon, England":"英國戴文","Devon, England":"英國戴文","lifeSummary":"William Cole是William Cole的兒子，於1160年出生在英國英格蘭戴文希迪斯利。他於大約1185年與Lady Ysabella在英國英格蘭可瓦爾特魯羅結婚。他們至少是1個兒子的父母。他去世於1243年在他的家鄉享年83歲。"},"zh-hans":{"1160–1243":"1160年–1243年","1160–1201":"1160年–1201年","1185–1273":"1185年–1273年","1140–1180":"1140年–1180年","1215":"1215年","1224":"1224年","1201":"1201年","1243":"1243年","1185":"1185年","1273":"1273年","1140":"1140年","Abt 1160":"大约1160年","1160":"1160年","about 1185":"大约1185年","1180":"1180年","Tiverton, Devon, England":"英国戴文迪維頓","Truro, Cornwall, England, United Kingdom":"英国英格兰可瓦爾特魯羅","Hittsleigh, Devon, England":"英国英格兰戴文希迪斯利","Hutenesleigh, Devon, England":"英国戴文","Devon, England":"英国戴文","lifeSummary":"William Cole是William Cole的儿子，于1160年出生在英国英格兰戴文希迪斯利。他于大约1185年与Lady Ysabella在英国英格兰可瓦爾特魯羅结婚。他们至少是1个儿子的父母。他去世于1243年在他的家乡享年83岁。"},"hr":{"1160–1243":"1160.–1243.","1160–1201":"1160.–1201.","1185–1273":"1185.–1273","1140–1180":"1140–1180.","1215":"1215","1224":"1224","1201":"1201.","1243":"1243.","1185":"1185.","1273":"1273","1140":"1140","Abt 1160":"oko 1160.","1160":"1160.","about 1185":"oko 1185.","1180":"1180.","Tiverton, Devon, England":"Tiverton, Devon, England","Truro, Cornwall, England, United Kingdom":"Truro, Cornwall, Engleska, United Kingdom","Hittsleigh, Devon, England":"Hittisleigh, Devon, Engleska, United Kingdom","Hutenesleigh, Devon, England":"Devon, England","Devon, England":"Devon, England"},"cs":{"1160–1243":"1160–1243","1160–1201":"1160–1201","1185–1273":"1185–1273","1140–1180":"1140–1180","1215":"1215","1224":"1224","1201":"1201","1243":"1243","1185":"1185","1273":"1273","1140":"1140","Abt 1160":"okolo 1160","1160":"1160","about 1185":"okolo 1185","1180":"1180","Tiverton, Devon, England":"Tiverton, Devon, Anglie","Truro, Cornwall, England, United Kingdom":"Truro, Cornwall, Anglie, United Kingdom","Hittsleigh, Devon, England":"Hittisleigh, Devon, Anglie, United Kingdom","Hutenesleigh, Devon, England":"Devon, Anglie","Devon, England":"Devon, Anglie"},"da":{"1160–1243":"1160–1243","1160–1201":"1160–1201","1185–1273":"1185–1273","1140–1180":"1140–1180","1215":"1215","1224":"1224","1201":"1201","1243":"1243","1185":"1185","1273":"1273","1140":"1140","Abt 1160":"omkring 1160","1160":"1160","about 1185":"omkring 1185","1180":"1180","Tiverton, Devon, England":"Tiverton, Devon, England","Truro, Cornwall, England, United Kingdom":"Truro, Cornwall, England, United Kingdom","Hittsleigh, Devon, England":"Hittisleigh, Devon, England, United Kingdom","Hutenesleigh, Devon, England":"Devon, England","Devon, England":"Devon, England"},"nl":{"1160–1243":"1160–1243","1160–1201":"1160–1201","1185–1273":"1185–1273","1140–1180":"1140–1180","1215":"1215","1224":"1224","1201":"1201","1243":"1243","1185":"1185","1273":"1273","1140":"1140","Abt 1160":"circa 1160","1160":"1160","about 1185":"circa 1185","1180":"1180","Tiverton, Devon, England":"Tiverton, Devon, England","Truro, Cornwall, England, United Kingdom":"Truro, Cornwall, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Hittsleigh, Devon, England":"Hittisleigh, Devon, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Hutenesleigh, Devon, England":"Devon, England","Devon, England":"Devon, England"},"en":{"1160–1243":"1160–1243","1160–1201":"1160–1201","1185–1273":"1185–1273","1140–1180":"1140–1180","1215":"1215","1224":"1224","1201":"1201","1243":"1243","1185":"1185","1273":"1273","1140":"1140","Abt 1160":"about 1160","1160":"1160","about 1185":"about 1185","1180":"1180","Tiverton, Devon, England":"Tiverton, Devon, England","Truro, Cornwall, England, United Kingdom":"Truro, Cornwall, England, United Kingdom","Hittsleigh, Devon, England":"Hittisleigh, Devon, England, United Kingdom","Hutenesleigh, Devon, England":"Devon, England","Devon, England":"Devon, England","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Cole","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English: usually from the Middle English and Old French personal name <i>Col(e)</i>, <i>Coll(e)</i>, <i>Coul(e)</i>, a pet form of <i>Nicol</i> (see   Nichol   and   Nicholas  ), a common personal name from the mid 13th century onward. English families with this name migrated to Scotland and to Ulster (especially Fermanagh).","English: occasionally perhaps from a different (early) Middle English personal name <i>Col</i>, of native English or Scandinavian origin. Old English <i>Cola</i> was originally a nickname from Old English <i>col</i> ‘coal’ in the sense ‘coal-black (of hair), swarthy’ and is the probable source of most of the examples in Domesday Book. In the northern and eastern counties of England settled by Vikings in the 10th and 11th centuries, alternative sources are Old Norse <i>Kolr</i> and <i>Koli</i> (either from a nickname ‘the swarthy one’ or a short form of names in <i>Kol-</i>), and Old Norse <i>Kollr</i> (from a nickname, perhaps ‘the bald one’).","English: nickname for someone with swarthy skin or black hair, from Middle English <i>col</i>, coul(e) ‘charcoal, coal’ (Old English <i>col</i>)."],"variants":[{"name":"Colton","meanings":["English (Yorkshire and Nottinghamshire): habitational name from any of various places called Colton in England. Examples in Norfolk, Staffordshire, and North Yorkshire are from the Old English personal name <i>Cola</i> (or the cognate Old Norse <i>Koli</i>; see   Cole   2) + Old English <i>tūn</i> ‘enclosure, settlement’. The place so named in Somerset has as its first element the Old English personal name <i>Cūla</i> (of uncertain origin). The one in Cumbria has a river name apparently derived from a Celtic word meaning ‘hazel’. This English name is also common in Ireland; it was the name of a bishop of Derry in 1397. There seems also to have been confusion with   Culliton  .","Scottish and Irish (Monaghan): shortened and altered form of Gaelic <b>Mac Haldan</b>, ‘son of <i>Haldan</i>’, see   Haldane  ."]},{"name":"Colclough","meanings":["English (Staffordshire and Cheshire): habitational name from Cowclough in the parish of Whitworth, Lancashire, earlier recorded as <i>Colleclogh</i>, probably named with the Old English byname <i>Cola</i> (see   Cole   2) + Old English <i>clōh</i> ‘ravine’."]},{"name":"Calcote","meanings":["English: habitational name from any of numerous places (in Bedfordshire, Berkshire, Cambridgeshire, Cheshire, Northamptonshire, Warwickshire, and elsewhere) named Caldecote or Caldecott, from Old English <i>cald</i> ‘cold’ + <i>cot</i> ‘cottage, dwelling’. It has been suggested that in Old English this expression denoted an unattended shelter for wayfarers, although in fact some places with this name were of considerable status by 1086, when they appear in Domesday Book. In some instances this and some of the other shortened forms may have arisen from Calcot in Berkshire, Collacott(s) in Devon, or Calcutt in Wiltshire, in all of which the first element apparently comes from the Old English personal name <i>Cola</i> (see   Cole   2) or the word <i>col</i> ‘(char)coal’, in which case the meaning would be something like ‘coalshed’."]},{"name":"Collignon","meanings":["French and Walloon: from a shortened pet form (see   Cole   and   Colle  ) of the French personal name <i>Nicolas</i> (see   Nicholas  )."]},{"name":"Colling","meanings":["English (northern England and Devon): from the Old Norse personal name <i>Kollungr</i>, a derivative of <i>Koli</i>, or from Old English <i>Colling</i>, a derivative of <i>Cola</i> (see   Cole  ). Alternatively, from a pet form of the personal name <i>Col(l)</i>, a pet form of   Nicholas   (see also   Colin  ).","German: variant of   Kolling   and, in North America, (also) an altered form of this."]},{"name":"Collard","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  French Donat, Normand, Octave, Adelard, Aldor, Andre, Armand, Emile, Germaine, Marcel.","English (southern), French, and Walloon: from a diminutive of the Middle English and Old French personal name <i>Col(e)</i>, a pet form of <i>Nic(h)olas</i> (see   Cole  ), formed with the Old French suffix <i>-ard</i>."]},{"name":"Coale","meanings":["English: post-medieval form of   Cole  . This surname is now rare in Britain."]},{"name":"Coles","meanings":["English (southern): variant of   Cole  , with genitival or post-medieval excrescent <i>-s</i>."]},{"name":"Nichol","meanings":["Scottish and northern English: from the Middle English personal name <i>Nic(h)ol(e)</i>, a vernacular form of <i>Nic(h)olas</i> (see   Nicholas  ). Compare   Nickel   and   Nicol  .","In some cases also an American shortened and altered form of Greek   Nikolas  , its variant   Nicolas  , or of any of various derivatives of the personal name <i>Nikola(o)s</i> ‘Nicholas’, including <b>Nikolis</b> (see   Nicoli  ). Compare   Nicholas   and   Nicol  ."]},{"name":"Coalson","meanings":["English: patronymic from   Cole  ."]}]},{"name":"William","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Probably the most successful of all the Old French names of Germanic origin that were introduced to England by the Normans. It is derived from Germanic <i>wil</i> ‘will, desire’ + <i>helm</i> ‘helmet, protection’. The fact that it was borne by the Conqueror himself does not seem to have inhibited its favour with the ‘conquered’ population: in the first century after the Conquest it was the commonest male name of all, and not only among the Normans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705187,"age":55,"year":"1215","julianDay":2164830,"title":"Magna Carta","description":"King John of England agreed to a charter of rights called the Magna Carta. The document was originally drafted by the Archbishop of Canterbury to establish peace between King John and a group of rebel barons. The Magna Carta was completed in 1215 and is now considered to be one of the greatest constitutional documents of all time.","url":"https://www.nationalarchives.gov.uk/education/medieval/magna-carta/","urlTitle":"National Archives - Magna Carta","jurisdictionLevel":1},{"id":1705188,"age":64,"year":"1224","julianDay":2168117,"title":"France Declares War on England","description":"France declared war on England as Louis VIII of France attacked Poitou and northern Gascony.","jurisdictionLevel":1}],"lifeSummary":"William Cole was born in 1160, in Hittisleigh, Devon, England, United Kingdom as the son of William Cole. He married Lady Ysabella about 1185, in Truro, Cornwall, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 1 son. He died in 1243, in his hometown, at the age of 83."},"et":{"1160–1243":"1160–1243","1160–1201":"1160–1201","1185–1273":"1185–1273","1140–1180":"1140–1180","1215":"1215","1224":"1224","1201":"1201","1243":"1243","1185":"1185","1273":"1273","1140":"1140","Abt 1160":"umbes 1160","1160":"1160","about 1185":"umbes 1185","1180":"1180","Tiverton, Devon, England":"Tiverton, Devon, England","Truro, Cornwall, England, United Kingdom":"Truro, Cornwall, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Hittsleigh, Devon, England":"Hittisleigh, Devon, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Hutenesleigh, Devon, England":"Devon, England","Devon, England":"Devon, England"},"fi":{"1160–1243":"1160–1243","1160–1201":"1160–1201","1185–1273":"1185–1273","1140–1180":"1140–1180","1215":"1215","1224":"1224","1201":"1201","1243":"1243","1185":"1185","1273":"1273","1140":"1140","Abt 1160":"noin 1160","1160":"1160","about 1185":"noin 1185","1180":"1180","Tiverton, Devon, England":"Tiverton, Devon, England","Truro, Cornwall, England, United Kingdom":"Truro, Cornwall, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Hittsleigh, Devon, England":"Hittisleigh, Devon, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Hutenesleigh, Devon, England":"Devon, England","Devon, England":"Devon, England"},"fr"